SIMPLE: acetanilide
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: acetanilide
<hw>ac`et*an"i*lide</hw> <pr>(⟦acr⟧s`⟦ecr⟧t*⟦acr⟧n"⟦icr⟧*l⟦icr⟧d)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Acet</ets>yl + <ets>anilide</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Med., Chem.)</fld> <def>An amide formed from aniline and an acetyl
group (<chform>C6H5.NH.CO.CH3</chform>); it is a white crystalline
compound used as an analgesic and also as an antipyretic. It has
molecular weight 135.16.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>acetanilid</asp>]</altsp> <ver>AS</ver>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> phenylacetamide, N-phenylacetamide, antifebrin,
antifebrine, acetylaminobenzene, acetylaniline</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source> + <source>AS</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Acetarious</ent>⟦br⟧
